All data downloaded from the BEA here. Variable descriptions can be found here.

BEA region codes:

  1. New England (Connecticut, Maine, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, Rhode Island, and Vermont);
  2. Mideast (Delaware, District of Columbia, Maryland, New Jersey, New York, and Pennsylvania);
  3. Great Lakes (Illinois, Indiana, Michigan, Ohio, and Wisconsin);
  4. Plains (Iowa, Kansas, Minnesota, Missouri, Nebraska, North Dakota, and South Dakota);
  5. Southeast (Alabama, Arkansas, Florida, Georgia, Kentucky, Louisiana, Mississippi, North Carolina, South Carolina, Tennessee, Virginia, and West Virginia);
  6. Southwest (Arizona, New Mexico, Oklahoma, and Texas);
  7. Rocky Mountain (Colorado, Idaho, Montana, Utah, and Wyoming); and
  8. Far West (Alaska, California, Hawaii, Nevada, Oregon, and Washington).
source("BEA_func.R")
source("BEA_load.R")
  • CAGDP11 - contributions to percent change in real GDP
  • CAGDP1 - GDP summary by county
  • CAEMP25N - total full-time and part-time employment by NAICS
  • CAEMP25S - total full- and part-time employment by SIC
  • CAINC1 - annual personal income by county
  • CAINC45 - farm income and expenses
  • CAINC4 - personal income and employment by major component
  • CAINC5N - personal income by major component by NAICS
  • CAINC5S - personal income by major component by SIC
  • CAINC6N - compensation of employees by NAICS
  • CAINC6S - compensation of employees by SIC
  • CAINC30 - economic profile by county

(many more on website to explore)

CAINC45 - Farm income and expenses

farms <- clean_BEA("./data/CAINC45__ALL_AREAS_1969_2019.csv")
unique(farms$Description)

farms %>%
  filter(Description == "Equals: Farm earnings",
         GEOID %in% unique(counties$GEOID)) %>%
  ggplot(.) +
  geom_point(aes(x = YEAR, y = value, color = Region)) +
  project_theme

farms %>%
  filter(Description == "Equals: Farm earnings",
         GEOID %in% unique(counties$GEOID)) %>%
  ggplot(.) +
  geom_boxplot(aes(x = as.factor(YEAR), y = value)) +
  project_theme

delta_earnings <- farms %>%
  filter(Description == "Equals: Farm earnings",
         GEOID %in% unique(counties$GEOID)) %>%
  group_by(GEOID) %>%
  summarize(DELTA = value[YEAR == max(YEAR)] - value[YEAR == min(YEAR)]) 
delta_earnings <- merge(counties, delta_earnings, by = "GEOID")
delta_earnings$LOSERS <- ifelse(delta_earnings$DELTA < 0, "Decrease", "Increase") 

ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = delta_earnings %>% filter(LOSERS == "Decrease"), aes(fill = DELTA), color = "transparent") +
  geom_sf(data = states, fill = "transparent", color = "dark gray") +
  map_theme +
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "dark red", high = "#FFCCCB") +
  labs(title = "Declining Profitability of American Farms",
       subtitle = "Change in earnings from 1969 to 2019",
      fill = "Thousands of dollars") +
  theme(legend.position = "right")

ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = delta_earnings %>% filter(LOSERS == "Increase"), aes(fill = DELTA), color = "transparent") +
  geom_sf(data = states, fill = "transparent", color = "dark gray") +
  map_theme +
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "#eff7fa", high = "dark blue") +
  labs(title = "Where are American farmers marking more money?",
       subtitle = "Regions with an increase in earnings from 1969 to 2019",
      fill = "Thousands of dollars") +
  theme(legend.position = "right")

delta_earnings$DELTA_CROP <- ifelse(delta_earnings$DELTA > 80000, 80000, delta_earnings$DELTA)
ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = delta_earnings, aes(fill = DELTA_CROP), color = "transparent") +
  geom_sf(data = states, fill = "transparent", color = "dark gray") +
  map_theme +
  scale_fill_gradient2(low = "dark red", mid = "white", high = "dark blue", limits = c(-80000, 80000)) +
  labs(title = "Change in farm earnings from 1969 to 2019",
      fill = "Thousands of dollars") +
  theme(legend.position = "right")
